:set path+=**
:set path?

display all matching files with "tab complete"
:set wildmenu

:find filename
:find *.cpp

autocomplete open any buffer
:b previ

will open if previ is a unique substring of files in the ":ls" buffer


run terminal command
$ ctags -R .
to generate tags for all files inside of the current folder

jump to tag under cursor
ctrl+]
find every instance of the tag under cursor
g+ctrl+]
go back to previous tag jump
ctrl+t

autocomplete
autocompleted
^x^n for current file
^x^f for filenames
^x^] for tags
^n default autocomplete

^e for exit completion and stay in insertion
